The problem of colored orthogonal range searching is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and databases, and has been extensively studied in the literature. This paper presents a new variant of the problem, which is focused on finding frequent colors in rectangles. This problem is relevant to many applications, such as data mining, information retrieval, and image processing. Given the focus on data structures and algorithms, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DB (Databases), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.DM (Data Mining).
